natspec.author: Xfai

Approval(address,address,uint256).details: Emitted when `owner` enables `approved` to manage the `tokenId` token.

ApprovalForAll(address,address,bool).details: Emitted when `owner` enables or disables (`approved`) `operator` to manage all of its assets.

Transfer(address,address,uint256).details: Emitted when `tokenId` token is transferred from `from` to `to`.

INFTShares(uint256).notice: Mapping from token ID to share

boost(uint256).details: This low-level function should be called from a contract which performs important safety checks
boost(uint256).notice: Boosts the share value of an INFT, the share of which is determined by the amount of the underlying token sent to the DexfaiFactory

params._tokenID: The token ID of an INFT

returns.share: The share value added to an INFT

params._expectedMints: The number of pre-mints before minting is available
params._factory: The address of the Xfai factory contract
params._initialReserve: The initial reserve used during deployment
params._underlyingToken: The address of the ERC20 token used as the underlying token for the INFT

getStates().notice: Function used to fetch contract states

returns._0: The reserve used during contract initialization, the reserve of the underlying token, and the total number of shares issued

harvestETH(uint256,uint256).notice: Harvests INFT fees from the INFT contract

harvestToken(address,uint256,uint256).notice: Harvests INFT fees from the INFT contract

params._token: The address of an ERC20 token

harvestedBalance(address).notice: Mapping from token address to harvested amounts. harvestedBalance shows how much of a token has been harvested so far from the contract.

initialReserve().notice: Initial reserve set at during deployment. Does count as part of INFT reserve

mint(address).details: This low-level function should be called from a contract which performs important safety checks
mint(address).notice: Creates a new INFT, the share of which is determined by the amount of the underlying token sent to the Xfai factory

params._to: The address to which the newly minted INFT should be sent to

returns.share: The share value of the INFT
returns.tokenID: The id of the newly minted INFT

premint(address[],uint256[]).details: Can only be called by the owner
premint(address[],uint256[]).notice: preMint is used to mint the legacy NFTs before minting is enabled

params._initialShares: the share array of the legacy nft holders
params._legacyLNFTHolders: the address array of the legacy nft holders

reserve().notice: The reserve of underlyingToken within the INFT contract

setBaseURI(string).details: setBaseURI can be called only by the contract owner
setBaseURI(string).notice: Function used to set the baseURI of the NFT

params._newBaseURI: the new baseURI string for the NFT

shareToTokenAmount(uint256,address).notice: Computes the amount of _token fees collected for a given _tokenID

params._token: the address of an ERC20 token
params._tokenID: The token ID of an INFT

returns.harvestedShares: The amount of shares harvested for a given pool
returns.share2amount: The total amount of _token that a given _tokenID can harvest

sharesHarvestedByPool(address,uint256).notice: Mapping from token address to token ID to token share

totalSharesHarvestedByPool(address).notice: Mapping from token address to total share for a token
